You are here: Salesforce Help

The CRM Analytics home page surfaces lists of items suggested for you based on your usage and your org. Two of the lists employ CRM Analytics intelligence to pinpoint important analytics, show what’s popular, and increase discoverability.

Smart recommendations appear as soon as you start working in CRM Analytics. They adhere to CRM Analytics user sharing rules and row-level security. Smart recommendation cards show only dashboards that you can access.

Jump Back In lists dashboards you viewed lately that are also popular with colleagues in your org.
Discover New Items lists dashboards you haven’t seen but could be relevant to you, based on their popularity over the last 30 days.
CRM Analytics learns what to recommend as you search and query.
title: Smart Recommendations in CRM Analytics
